description: Use ASCII punctuation only in code, docs, and user-facing strings.
alwaysApply: true
---

# ASCII Punctuation

- Never use the em dash character (`—`, U+2014) in this repository.
- Use a hyphen-minus (`-`) instead for breaks in prose, lists, and UI copy.
- Apply the same rule to comments, docstrings, markdown, commit messages, and
  error strings generated by the project.
